titleInfo.title: Burgett, Inc. v. American Zurich Insurance Company
titleInfo.subTitle: MEMORANDUM AND ORDER signed by Judge Morrison C. England, Jr on 11/22/11: Plaintiff's motion for summary judgment as to Defendant's duty to defend the underlying Persis action is GRANTED 8. Plaintiff is awarded reasonable attorneys' fees for breach of its duty to defend the underlying Persis action. However, the Court requires additional briefing as to the amount of attorneys' fees to which Plaintiff is claiming. Such additional briefing from Plaintiff is to be filed not later than forty-five (45) days after this electronic order is filed. The Court orders that Plaintiff is not entitled to prejudgment interest. (Kaminski, H)
